msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:6
msgid "Here is a list of situations in which we use the main domain concept:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to expose the web portal: currently the web portal is only reachable through "
"the main domain address (could be changed for multi tenant support in future)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to define the hostname of the machine: we believe we do this to avoid some "
"sudo errors (may be it's not relvant anymore or could be made in /etc/hosts)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to TLS encrypt SMTP and dovecot: so user should define the main domain in "
"their email client to avoid TLS warning"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"To be able to do mail forwarding using the main domain as [Sender Rewriting "
"Scheme Domain](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sender_Rewriting_Scheme)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to define default email as (root@ abuse@) but we probably should do it on "
"all parent domain instead"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to define `myhostname` in postfix config, used as EHLO and reverseDNS "
"(refering to [MX Toolbox](https://mxtoolbox.com/emailhealth) test it should "
"be a FQDN, so a subdomain)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to generate the self-signed Local Authority: having just one allow to upload "
"it in a browser and get an x509 authenticated https connexion."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
#: docs/dev/80.core/maindomain.mdx:15
msgid ""
"to define default xmpp DNS field: dns field are only set on the main domain "
"by default"
msgstr ""

